{"recommendationid": "11141466", "author": {"steamid": "76561197969871162", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 5, "playtime_forever": 215, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 182, "last_played": 1429811977}, "language": "english", "review": "Game crashes to desktop after about 5 mins of play although my system meets the minimum requirements. I went through a month of following automated help desk messages after I opened a ticket with Ubisoft ("Send us your dxdiag info, delete save games and so on) until they finally said that they can't help me and that I'd have to weait for a patch which I don't expect to ever appear.

About the gameplay (as far as I could play): Can't tell you about the story as I didn't get past the 2nd mission, yet the hacking possibilities in that stage of the game seem rather simple: Switch traffic lights, open draw bridges, blow up steam pipes, maybe two or three more. But you get to see them quite soon and I guess there isn't much after that.
Also, you never see any cops around (even when driving over people and causing general mayhem) until you break any scripted "laws" which causes them to spawn all of a sudden and swarm all over you. I think we've all seen other open world games (GTA series) which have been doing better at this years before this was released.", "timestamp_created": 1404858364, "timestamp_updated": 1404858364, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 1, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11166459", "author": {"steamid": "76561198052831659", "num_games_owned": 1325, "num_reviews": 61, "playtime_forever": 1207, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 1022, "last_played": 1404742779}, "language": "koreana", "review": " 핸드폰과 해킹이라는 소재를 활용한 오픈 월드 액션 어드벤처 게임입니다. 플레이어는 핸드폰을 이용하는 다재다능한 해커가 되어, 도심속에서 자경단원으로 활동하며, 이야기를 펼쳐나가게 됩니다. 해킹을 통해, 데이터를 빼오는 것 뿐만 아니라, 가스 벨브를 폭파 시키거나, 지역을 정전시키는 등의 현대 사회에 어울리는 슈퍼 파워를 사용할 수 있게 됩니다. 탄탄한 스토리와 다양한 컨텐츠 그리고 멀티 플레이 경쟁 요소까지 완성도 높은 게임성을 보여 줍니다. 성장 요소부터 도전 요소 그리고 멋진 그래픽을 가진 작품입니다.

장점: 멋진 그래픽, 다양한 컨텐츠, 수많은 확장 요소(DLC)
단점: 약간 어려운 난이도(경찰 또는 추격 등 운전 관련 컨텐츠의 난이도가 높은 편)", "timestamp_created": 1405000175, "timestamp_updated": 1405000175, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 5, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.569011688232421875", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11174639", "author": {"steamid": "76561198028278060", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 2, "playtime_forever": 3887, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 3777, "last_played": 1405047069}, "language": "english", "review": "Score: 8.5/10

Overall great game with a decent story. The driving dynamics in this game are excellent, which is a pretty important factor in my book when you've got an open world game. If you expect this game to have an exact map of Chicago, then you'll be disappointed - but given to scale of the game it's a good effort.

Biggest cons of this game is the fact that it runs like sh#t... Any of those comments that say "well it's a next gen game" is a load of crap - this game was poorly optimized for the PC platform, end of discussion. I have an i7-970, with two GTX 580s in SLI and it struggles with this game on max settings. If you have an NVIDIA GPU, and you have GeForce Experience installed allow that to optimize the game setting for you.", "timestamp_created": 1405035987, "timestamp_updated": 1405035987, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11176426", "author": {"steamid": "76561197970421860", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 38, "playtime_forever": 3686, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2907, "last_played": 1406224161}, "language": "english", "review": "A buggy broken mess. This game crashed more frequently and more catastrophically than Skyrim, and I play Skyrim with 134 mods. Your save games will get corrupted. You will lose progress. It will crater at the most inconvenient spots. If you're incredibly lucky, you may be able to recover some of that lost time. But the biggest challenge in this game is enduring the constant bugs, crashes and data loss.

And don't expect UbiSoft to care. If their cloud service eats your games, their recommended fix is to not use their cloud service in favour of a third party program like Dropbox. Their first "patch" fixed performance issues by hobbling the rendering, and they haven't addressed the crashes at all. The only patch they've released since is a DLC patch for "new content" (read: pre-order bonuses repackaged as fresh content).

The plot is supposed to be a cautionary tale about overdependence on integrated technology, but the bigger lesson I learned is that you can't demand a refund for inferior products you buy on a digital platform. The true villains of this game are the PC porting team. Avoid, avoid, avoid.", "timestamp_created": 1405046380, "timestamp_updated": 1405046380, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11190824", "author": {"steamid": "76561197977077101", "num_games_owned": 275, "num_reviews": 31, "playtime_forever": 1011, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 140, "last_played": 1462269894}, "language": "english", "review": "If you're not a fan of 3rd person controller based games then do not buy this for PC gaming.

The keyboard controls are horrid and there's no ability to switch to 1st person meaning it's an annoying task to just navigate around. I like the open world gameplay but it's just ruined (for me) by the obvious lack of finese a mouse/keyboard game should have.

I would recommend Deus Ex instead if you haven't played that, especially given the price.", "timestamp_created": 1405121218, "timestamp_updated": 1405121244, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 2, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": false, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11273844", "author": {"steamid": "76561198114183227", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 17, "playtime_forever": 4004, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2150, "last_played": 1429105918}, "language": "english", "review": "Watch_Dogs is one of the best games I have ever played pesonally. The campaign was fantastic and took me nearly 40 hours to complete so it is lengthy but not repitive. The only problem i had with the campaign was the suspect was pretty predictable. However the levels let you inavate on how you were to do them my favourite being 'Little Sister'. The DLC's that I currently have access to are very good and I can't wait until I can play as T-bone. Another of my favourite things was the honour level it really can be usefull; however if you are ignorant you are punished heavily when commiting crimes! 

All in all I think that this is a good game and is worth its cost.
WELL DONE UBISOFT hats off to you sirs and madames.", "timestamp_created": 1405525840, "timestamp_updated": 1405525840, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 1, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.476190477609634399", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11311896", "author": {"steamid": "76561198022753752", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 1, "playtime_forever": 4033, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2978, "last_played": 1535687698}, "language": "english", "review": "Although the game is not what we first saw in the E3 hype, the game is still fun to play through.  Storyline is alright but you get a feeling very quickly that this guy - Aiden - is total douche (is that how you spell it).  The side quests are plenty, albeit repetetive whithin their own kind.  Gang hideouts are FUN! I mean, even if I die here and there, I come back with different option on how to approach the main target and knock him out and how to kill the other ones.  You get to unlock an arsenal of weapons, but the SpecOps 1911 (Silenced) is probably the one you'll use 90% in story mode, and the high-grade shotgun/automatic weapon/granade launcher online.

Online challenges are not difficult, but they do take some time to get into. It's respectable I think. Unlockables include skills, weapons and cars, and overall there's plenty of that to go around. Police are hard as shit when they are on your balls but just drive away on a boat on the river and you'll be ok - no marine force to follow you out of the police radar.  The hacking is is good the first few tries but sometimes the hacking in side quests (like any other side quest) tends to get repetetive.

Overall, it's a good adventure/action game that borrows elements from Splinter Cell's sneak/weapon system and Assasin Creed's parkouring.  It's not worth $60, but it is fun, I'd say >$40 worth if you want to put a price for your fun level.", "timestamp_created": 1405735776, "timestamp_updated": 1405735776, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11378740", "author": {"steamid": "76561198020925045", "num_games_owned": 234, "num_reviews": 2, "playtime_forever": 2270, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2054, "last_played": 1500560194}, "language": "english", "review": "Watch Dogs was quite the disappointment. I wanted to like it so bad and I even told myself that I liked it for the 35 hours that I have played. But then I realized: This game is simply not good. The story is weak, the hacking is very unsatisfying, and the driving mechanics are totally whack. However, it is an open-world game, which I do love, and the graphics engine is incredible in my opinion. It just felt very unfinished. They could have done much better. 

I wouldn't recommend this game at its current price. If it drops to $15 or $20? Maybe.

But again, this is my opinion. Take it as you will.", "timestamp_created": 1406136587, "timestamp_updated": 1449939768, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 2, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11385746", "author": {"steamid": "76561197970426093", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 56, "playtime_forever": 5263, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 5008, "last_played": 1411694858}, "language": "english", "review": "The hands-down best part of Watch Dogs is the artwork and city design.  I've never seen such detail in my 3 decades of PC gaming and I enjoy just walking around and taking in the scenery.  The wet shaders during rain storms and the atmosphere down in the Wards at night almost evokes a sense of melencholy and perhaps even despair.  The lighting engine is like non other (except the Metro 2033 games) and I've had several people look at screenshots and they thought they were photos until I told them it was a game!  Without a doubt, the real talent behind this game are the artists.  The cut scenes are great and the acting is top-notch, which is par for the course with Ubisoft games.

I NEVER had any technical issues running this game, even with all details turned on except for the "ultra" textures, which didn't make any noticeable difference in quality when it was turned on anyway.  The driving model sucks a$$, but it IS learnable, and once I had it mastered, the car chases were fun and intense.  Even more so than GTA.  However, that fun went only to a certain degree, because once your "heat level" with the cops went above 3, they attacked with a ridiculous level of absurdity that is not even remotely realistic except perhaps in the mind of a sadist with an IQ of 80 or less.  The worst part of that is the sniper from the helicopter, which locks on to you with perfect stability and NEVER misses.... ever.  That is just plain stupid, and whomever it was at Ubisoft who decided that was a good idea... I pray for your violent death.  F**k you.

For that reason, and also just because I can, I give this game a thumbs down.", "timestamp_created": 1406177090, "timestamp_updated": 1406177090, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.415610671043395996", "comment_count": 2, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11401382", "author": {"steamid": "76561198076113544", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 14, "playtime_forever": 1648, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 1648, "last_played": 1402141854}, "language": "russian", "review": "Прошёл игру с упоением. понравилось всё, сюжет, графика, атмосфера чикаго, возможнось хакнуть чейнибудь девайс. Очень порадовало что в ингре очень качественно переведены ВСЕ диалоги. 
Возможность хакнуть разводной мост, чтобы замутить себе трамплин, это уже круто:)

Так что да. я рекомендую эту игру всем любителям GTA жанра, и особенно тем кому понравилось играть в Sleeping Dogs :)", "timestamp_created": 1406279514, "timestamp_updated": 1406279514, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11441361", "author": {"steamid": "76561198034875960", "num_games_owned": 8555, "num_reviews": 53, "playtime_forever": 5498, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 3884, "last_played": 1478522572}, "language": "koreana", "review": "추천과 비추사이에서 고민고민하다가, 추천으로 결정했습니다

'어쌔씬 크리드 시리즈'와 연관성이 있다고 하던데, 아직 어크 2까지만 해봐서 알수가 없더군요 ;ㅅ;

NPC들을 프로파일링해보면 앱스테르고에서 일한적 있다고 나오는 NPC들 있던데.. 설마 이게!?

최적화 부분은 2012년작 '고스트 리콘 퓨처 솔저'처럼 욕나오는 수준입니다만, 유저 패치로 그나마 낫더군요

하지만, 퓨처 솔저는 대부분의 유저가 플레이 가능했으나, 이게임은 사양문제로 많은 분들이 접할수 없다는...

그외 짜증났던 부분은 차량 조작감이 시뮬 레이싱에 가까워서, 자동차 추격전에서 종종 멘붕이... =_=;

참신한(?) 시도였던 온라인 해킹은 스토리나 퍼즐풀이에 열중해 있을때...

누군가 난입해 들어오면 욕나오는 부작용이 있습니다 (특히, CtOS 공격 퍼즐풀때 난입하면.. 진심 빡침 ㅠㅠ)


여튼.. 최적화와 사양문제만 아니었다면, 지금보다 많은 사랑을 받을수 있던 게임인것은 확실합니다", "timestamp_created": 1406502171, "timestamp_updated": 1406502238, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 4, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.545777976512908936", "comment_count": 2, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11470681", "author": {"steamid": "76561198074302262", "num_games_owned": 139, "num_reviews": 3, "playtime_forever": 4563, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2512, "last_played": 1467577479}, "language": "english", "review": "So far, this is the BEST GAME EVER, but it mellows down once you complete the story

hopefully there will be more missions, gang hideouts are fun, but fixer contracts and criminal convoys are very frusturating

all in all, this game isn't as bad as it is advertised, and uplay can be annoying, but it is still a great game", "timestamp_created": 1406677827, "timestamp_updated": 1406677827, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 1, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.49656069278717041", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11529936", "author": {"steamid": "76561198023503922", "num_games_owned": 185, "num_reviews": 4, "playtime_forever": 7582, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 7582, "last_played": 1407327994}, "language": "english", "review": "Yes, it's a good game. No, it's not a game-changer.

