10/10", "timestamp_created": 1407292456, "timestamp_updated": 1407292456, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 2, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.471947193145751953", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11707680", "author": {"steamid": "76561198041446121", "num_games_owned": 521, "num_reviews": 6, "playtime_forever": 2767, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2550, "last_played": 1431829281}, "language": "english", "review": "This was one of my most looked foward to games of the year. While some of the early problems seemed to sour some of the experience at first. Once I stopped worrying about trying to have all settings on high, I actually had a great time with the game.

I especially loved trying to knockout everyone instead of going in guns blazing, loved scouting out the lay of the land then start attacking.

When all is said and done, I had a great deal of fun playing the game and was entertained. In my opinion it's a game that should get some of your attention.", "timestamp_created": 1408060247, "timestamp_updated": 1408060247, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "11734586", "author": {"steamid": "76561197996976136", "num_games_owned": 772, "num_reviews": 4, "playtime_forever": 4031, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 3384, "last_played": 1466830062}, "language": "english", "review": "This game is a real mixed bag for me, but ultimately it's a 'win. The city and enviornment is stunningly detailed, it's an incredibly immersive place to explore. The multiplayer aspect of it is incredibly fun, being able to invade people's games (and have them seemlessly invade yours) is immensely satisfying. The gameplay elements themselves are also pretty interesting, certianly adds a bit of spice and variety over your usual first-person shooters or sandbox RPGs.

However, the engine needs some serious work. Like, serious work. It's certianly shiny in places, but the performance is abysmal (and I have a reasonably decent graphics card). The single-player campaign is also extremely disappointing, mostly due to Aiden Pierce having the personality and emotional capacity of a wooden spoon. There's aspects to the storyline that if emphasised a bit more would have really lent to the story overall, but they were kinda just minor side points and not really explored in any detail.

Ultimately, I *can* recommend this game, but not until the price drops a bit more and mostly for the multiplayer and the environment itself. If you're looking for a good plot and emotional storyline however, I suggest looking elsewhere.", "timestamp_created": 1408167256, "timestamp_updated": 1408167256, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 4, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.537972509860992432", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

