{"recommendationid": "12121409", "author": {"steamid": "76561198012472980", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 8, "playtime_forever": 5494, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 3783, "last_played": 1477216888}, "language": "english", "review": "This game is a really great revenge story set in Chicago in a near future where a big brother surveilance state controls society. The semi-realistic and deadly fights in the game force you into actively thinking about information and how to get an advantage in every situation. Very few missions will be approached with brute force unless demanded otherwise, but thats ok because it feels gooood when you outsmart the enemy. 

I found myself cruising around town for quite a few hours just enjoying the music and view of Chicago and its suburbs. It gave me pretty good driving skills avoiding pedetrians as you actually get punished when killing them by being reported to the police much easier than if you play the vigilante and target those that prey on the weak. The many side quests and funny games is a both a good distraction from the main story line but sometimes also gives you advantages (and a bonus mission at the end of a side quest line).

