", "timestamp_created": 1411481829, "timestamp_updated": 1411481829, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 30, "votes_funny": 1, "weighted_vote_score": "0.612085938453674316", "comment_count": 1, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "12204616", "author": {"steamid": "76561197976312757", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 168, "playtime_forever": 950, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 950, "last_played": 1411382149}, "language": "english", "review": "I was looking forward to this game for the longest time. The previews looked amazing and I counted the days until it was released, despite the delays. When it came out and I finally got to play it... let's just say that this game is the poster-boy for the dangers of over-hype.

If Grand Theft Auto and Assassin's creed had a bit of fun in a back alley one drunken night, then this would be what would pop out from between Assassin's Creed's legs 9 months later. It looked like such a beautiful child on the ultra-sound. When it was born, it seemed almost perfect and had such dreams. It promised that it would grow up to be the most amazing thing ever and take the world by storm. As time passed and it eventually blossomed into a full fledged game, however, people started to notice crippling deformities. Watch_Dogs also decided that instead of revolutionizing the very fabric of space and time, as it had promised, that it's ultimate goal was to become a part time data entry clerk for a used furniture shop, using it's free time to empty bed pans in the Geriatric ward of a hospital for curry addicts; not only that but it tried to make everyone else think that that was the coolest thing ever.

This is Watch_dogs. Buy it and weep within minutes at your forever lost money.", "timestamp_created": 1411492096, "timestamp_updated": 1411492096, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.458622068166732788", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "12250427", "author": {"steamid": "76561197992818490", "num_games_owned": 435, "num_reviews": 12, "playtime_forever": 3805, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 1764, "last_played": 1468964941}, "language": "english", "review": "The story is boring and predictable. I'm unable to be emotionally engaged in any of the characters. Side-quests are too similar and reminds me too much that this is a game. The people in the city doesn't feel as alive as I hoped. The world of GTA V feels much more alive in my opinion. Multiplayer stuff you try once and then never again.
One problem I see with this game is that you never lose your abilities. I know it is a cliché for certain games, but here it would probably work quite well. Yes, I know that there is one mission where your abilities are reduced, but it is basically just for a few minutes.

The game is not terrible, but the hype made it seem much better than it actually is. I'm sort of glad I played it, but one playthrough is more than enough.", "timestamp_created": 1411762054, "timestamp_updated": 1411762054, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 5, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.533205270767211914", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "12265558", "author": {"steamid": "76561198025315115", "num_games_owned": 643, "num_reviews": 24, "playtime_forever": 14764, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 8432, "last_played": 1723286938}, "language": "english", "review": "It's not really the most awesome game ever, but at least it got some really good content, a decent story line (a bit too short, but being Skyrim my previously plad game, I think I know why). It's a bit sad that it's not really a dynamic game, no choices, no hard decisions, the story is too linear. There are however a lot of side missions (with most of them a separete story, but most are just voice overs or pre-recorded messages).

The DLC Bad Blood is really cool and focusses even more on hacking stuff, but It's still more a shooting game, and I think that's bad. The game allows you to buy ammo and weapons, but you can just pick up weapons and ammo is automatically restocked when you die (which can happen a few times in missions). As a single player game I would not recommend this game at all, but what's really fun is the multiplayer part. Being hacked, hacking, tailing, being tailed, it's a really great gameplay mechanic, It's only sad that in order to get hacked, you have to wait. Of course, this is the great time to do some small objectives like scanning QR codes, or visiting every city spot, but after completing these the game has nothing left to offer you except for some fun side activities, or being hacked (or hacking other people, which is sometimes more a waiting game).

Do I recommend this game? I might, it's sad that the game sucks after completing it and you have to wait more than doing some real cool stuff, but it's a really great game!", "timestamp_created": 1411848202, "timestamp_updated": 1411848202, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

